Wait, but the server should use the client-generated id? The requirement says "Generate a stable id on the client when adding a todo so the optimistic item can be reconciled with the persisted record." So we can pass the id to the server and the server uses that id. That makes reconciliation easy - the id stays the same. Let me do that: server inserts with the provided id. Then reconcile just confirms. Actually reconcile with server truth means we replace the item with server result. But if ids match, we could just keep it. But to "reconcile with the server truth", let me replace with server-returned todo. Since id matches, it's fine either way. Let me replace to be safe.

